{"body": "Figuring out the correct IP is _the_ responsibility of the RemoteIp middleware, right? Folks shouldn't have to write a second middleware that deals in the same protocol details as RemoteIp in order to get RemoteIp to work correctly in what is a very common environment.\r\n\r\nI'm all for removing the spoof checking as well, but I think there needs to be a configuration option to say which of Client-Ip and X-Forwarded-For is accurate.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11798446", "created_at": "2013-01-02T01:16:17Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7980#issuecomment-11798446", "updated_at": "2013-01-02T01:16:17Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7980, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jfirebaugh", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a82409021ddf415a8027872b889c5f74?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9db597035f77a6c1167e05ca916801fa.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a82409021ddf415a8027872b889c5f74", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jfirebaugh", "type": "User", "id": 98601, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523db5b8bd354364b90095f2"}, "id": 11798446, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7980"}
